# Delivery Rule — How Cursor Should Work In This Repo

This repository already contains a working codebase.

## Always do this first
- inspect current structure before proposing changes
- restate the objective briefly
- identify affected existing modules/files
- propose the smallest correct refactor path
- call out assumptions and migration risks

## Preferred execution order
1. inspect existing code
2. map reusable modules
3. define minimal target changes
4. refactor types/contracts
5. refactor services/components
6. wire new capability
7. add/update tests
8. update docs only where useful

## Output style
- prefer incremental refactors over full rewrites
- produce production-oriented code
- avoid parallel unused scaffolding
- do not invent architecture inconsistent with the repo
- keep changes easy to review

## If blocked
- state exactly what existing code needs inspection
- propose the next safe incremental step
- do not jump to a rewrite unless necessary

## Quality bar
Every implementation should be:
- typed
- testable
- secure by default
- aligned with the current repo structure
- clearly migrated from the existing codebase toward the target architecture
